About the Role
DBRS Morningstar European Structured Finance team is looking for a senior addition to the team, to be based in Frankfurt. The role has management responsibilities and the successful candidate will head the European Structured Finance rating process quality assurance (QA) team. The QA team has an integral role in the rating process, serving as a link between the rating, global operations and compliance teams. The tasks of the team are diverse and broadly defined as ensuring adherence to the regulatory and compliance obligations during the rating process. The tasks range from monitoring adherence to DBRS Morningstar’s policies, procedures and guidelines, over proposing, implementing or overseeing the implementation of technical improvements, to contributing to the enhancement of DBRS Morningstar’s policies and procedures.
Job Responsibilities
Lead the QA team in monitoring the analytical staff’s adherence with DBRS Morningstar’s policies and procedures during the rating process and follow up when necessary;
Reporting to senior management and compliance, and follow up where needed, on various items related to policies and procedures, for example document retention, rating checklists, disclosures, annual reviews;
Design and deliver management reports as they relate to rating process, policies and procedures;
Liaise with compliance and analytical staff to ensure identified issues are remediated timely and effectively;
Collaborate with the compliance and operations department to develop ways to leverage technology to create efficiencies in the rating process;
Follow up and respond to compliance, analysts and management queries as they relate to policies and procedures and the adherence with those;
Analyse results of compliance monitoring and testing reviews and provide recommendations to mitigate the risk of future breaches;
Provide training on rating process and tools;
Work on projects that span the QA area (projects range from process improvement, technical efficiency enhancements of the rating process, system implementations and executing other strategic initiatives related to policies and procedures)
Assist other teams and management in project management.
Qualifications
Candidates should be willing to work in an environment with strong focus on team-work, have a strong worth ethic, organisational skills and the ability to multi-task. A strong attention to detail and affinity with IT is crucial for the role.
Completed a bachelor (or equivalent) degree in finance or a related area;
A Masters, CFA or accounting designation (enrollment or completion) are considered definite assets;
At least 4 years of experience developed in compliance, audit and/or regulatory analysis developed in financial services or accounting professions
Understanding of and/or professional experience with a credit rating agency;
Experience in monitoring adherence to corporate policies, procedures and other guidance documents;
Strong analytical and investigative skills, ability to extract trends and patterns from large data sets and sound judgment;
Proficiency in Microsoft Excel. Advanced knowledge and practical skills in using Word, PowerPoint and Outlook;
Affinity with IT, experience in data base management, knowledge of SQL is a plus;
Ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously while ensuring high quality results;
Demonstrated organisation skills with a very high attention to detail;
Team player with excellent problem-solving, communication, and negotiation skills;
Excellent written and oral English language skills;
Knowledge of another European language/s is a plus;
Permission to live and work in the European Union. This position requires occasional European travel.
Nice to have
Experience in managing a team
Experience interacting with employees at various levels of an organization;
About Us
DBRS Morningstar is a global credit ratings business, currently with 700 employees in eight offices globally. Formed through the July 2019 acquisition of DBRS by Morningstar, Inc., the ratings business is the fourth-largest provider of credit ratings in the world.
DBRS Morningstar is committed to empowering investor success, serving the market through leading-edge technology and raising the bar for the industry. DBRS Morningstar is a market leader in Canada, the U.S. and Europe in multiple asset classes.
DBRS Morningstar rates more than 2,600 issuers and 54,000 securities worldwide and is driven to bringing more clarity, diversity of opinion, and responsiveness to the ratings process. DBRS Morningstar’s approach and size provide the agility to respond to customers’ needs, while being large enough to provide the necessary expertise and resources.
